.TH "rtnl_register" 9 "rtnl_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rtnl_register \- Register a rtnetlink message type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rtnl_register
.BI "(int protocol "  ","
.BI "int msgtype "  ","
.BI "rtnl_doit_func doit "  ","
.BI "rtnl_dumpit_func dumpit "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "protocol" 12
Protocol family or PF_UNSPEC
.IP "msgtype" 12
rtnetlink message type
.IP "doit" 12
Function pointer called for each request message
.IP "dumpit" 12
Function pointer called for each dump request (NLM_F_DUMP) message
.IP "flags" 12
rtnl_link_flags to modifiy behaviour of doit/dumpit functions
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Registers the specified function pointers (at least one of them has
to be non-NULL) to be called whenever a request message for the
specified protocol family and message type is received.

The special protocol family PF_UNSPEC may be used to define fallback
function pointers for the case when no entry for the specific protocol
family exists.
